== Pasta ==

Fill and boil your #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @linguine{180%grams} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

== Bacon, Chicken and Mushrooms ==

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%grams}, @sliced mushrooms{80%grams} and
@British smoked bacon lardons{60%grams}.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden all over, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

== Veggies ==

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Cut the @Tenderstem® broccoli{150%grams} into thirds.

Once the mushrooms and bacon are golden, stir in the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}.

When the pasta has ~{4%minutes} left, add the broccoli to the same pan and cook for the
remaining time.

Once the pasta and broccoli are cooked, reserve some of the @reserved pasta water{100%ml},
then drain in a #colander{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to prevent it sticking.

== Sauce and Assembly ==

Stir the reserved pasta water, @creme fraiche{150%grams} and @chicken stock paste{10%grams}
into the mushrooms and bacon, simmer for ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the cooked pasta, broccoli and @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams} to the sauce
and gently toss to coat.

Add another splash of @water{} if the sauce is a bit thick. Season to taste with @salt{}
and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook so there's no pink in the middle of the chicken.

Share the bacon, chicken and mushroom linguine between your #bowls{}. Enjoy!